HEADWORD: Saxony
<hw>Sax"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after the
kingdom of <etsep>Saxony</etsep>, reputed to produce fine wool.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of glossy woolen cloth formerly much
used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Saxony yarn, or flannel made of it or similar
yarn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saxony yarn</ent>⟦br⟧
